sec.p:
There are also various optimization studies on SOFCs from various operational and microstructural aspects based on mathematical and artificial intelligence models. Bozorgmehri and Hamedi [16] proposed a neural network model of anode-supported SOFC. They used a genetic algorithm to optimize the neural network model to improve the performance of SOFC. Behzadi and Roshandel [17] implemented multi-objective optimization of SOFC stack by considering the effects of fuel utilization and hydrogen cost. Quddus et al. [18] implemented multi-objective optimization for oxidative coupling of methane using genetic algorithms by considering maximization of power and C2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
